Personally I think there are 3 main things that would improve mage class a lot.<br>
<br>
1. better pets.  maybe a pet buff (non dispellable) that raises the level, hitpoints, AC, and resists.  similar to BL pet buffs.  right now pets don't do enough damage vs higher level mobs and don't live long enough especially in AE fights.<br>
<br>
2. better nukes.  your gonna have to give wizards this also to shut them up but they could probably use it too, if you compare melee with ToV/Sleeper loot vs a similar caster...<br>
<br>
3. damage shields.  these should scale better.  33pt shield is OK vs a mob that hits for 140 and has 8000 hps but vs mobs that hit for 500's and have 100,000 hp?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Easy solution would be to make 60-70pt dmg shields for lvl 59-60 mages.  Even better but more work codewise would be shields that scale with how hard the hit was.  ie 150pt hit = 35 dmg, 400pt hit = 100dmg, 850pt hit = 200dmg (all about 25% dmg shield / hit ratio).  This would be great of course for uber mobs but also has the added benefit of not upsetting the balance vs blue mobs or in PVP.<br>
